6. Ultro damnatur] That is, the ‘delator‘ was caught in his own trap; the tables were turned on him. So far from getting Gaetulicus ruined, he got himself ruined. There could not be a better instance of the force of ‘ultro,’ a word to which in this sense Tacitus is decidedly partial.
